# HTML version (for Teamwork v1 API `content-type: HTML`)

```html
<p><strong>Dev QA: Automated test run - {VERDICT}</strong></p>
<p>The full QA suite has been run against <code>{baseUrl}</code> for <strong>{workblock}</strong>.</p>

<h4>Suite verdicts</h4>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Suite</th><th>Result</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>console</td><td>{verdict}</td></tr>
    <!-- ... one per suite -->
  </tbody>
</table>

<h4>Critical-path pages</h4>
<ul>
  <li><strong>{page}</strong>: {verdict}</li>
</ul>

<h4>Issues to action</h4>
<ol>
  <li><strong>{suite} / {page}</strong> - {title}<br>{detail}</li>
</ol>

<h4>Attached evidence</h4>
<ul>
  <li><strong>summary.md</strong> - text summary</li>
  <li><strong>report.html</strong> - full self-contained report</li>
</ul>
```

# Notes for the agent

- Pull the verdict, counts, and issues from `{outputDir}/summary.json` produced by `aggregate.mjs`.
- Attach `summary.md` by default; only attach `report.html` if the user explicitly asks (it's larger).
- Post on the workblock parent task or the explicit `config.teamwork.taskId`.
- Use the same prefix convention as other Claude-authored comments: `(I added this comment as a suggestion from Claude)`.
